title: For Sale/Trade:   AR 15 chambered in 6.8SPC (6.8X43mm) Cash or Trade
postcontent:
Up for sale or trade is a Palmetto State Armory AR15 chambered in the powerful 6.8 SPC round (6.8 X 43MM).  This is a nice rifle, featuring the softer shooting, mid-length D.I gas system.  

The rifle is the shortest possible length (a true 16.1"), while still being NFA compliant.  It has a 14.7" hammer forged barrel that is manufactured by FN which is commonly referred to as "machine gun" steel due to its use in the M249 and M240 machine guns.  The barrel is also double chrome lined, 1:10 twist, with a pinned/welded A2 flash hider which brings it to the legal length of 16.1". 

The rifle has a chrome BCG, fixed front sight,  6 position telescoping stock, and Blackhawk pistol grip.  Comes with a 25 round magazine AND flip up rear sight.  Will also come with PSA box.  

This is a very nice rifle.  I have yet to fire this one, I'm moving it to clear a little space in the safe.  I figured I didn't really need 5 AR 15's.  I could use some of the trades listed below or will sell for cash price listed.

I may separate the upper complete with BCG, 25 rd magazine and flip up sight.

title: For Sale:  9mm AR Rock River Upper/Double Diamond Glock Lower
location: Salt Lake City, Salt Lake City, Utah
postcontent:
I am selling one of my project AR's in 9mm. It has a Rock River Arms upper and a Double Diamond Law Enforcement lower that accepts Glock 9mm magazines (There are NO magazines included). It is also running a Rock River 9mm bolt that has been ramped and cut to work with Glock magazines and provide greater overall reliability. It has a low profile gas block and is ready to accept optics. The buffer is the famous 9-Q buffer weighing 8.5 ounces. It also has an extra power spring from Wolff. This makes the gun (which is blowback) run smoother and will extend the life of the internals. I have also installed an ambidextrous charging handle latch.

It is basically brand new with less than 100 rounds through it. I had a local gunsmith look at it to see if we needed to alter anything and I did slim down the bolt release to make it run a little smoother. It is very accurate!!! I could hit the leaves of a dueling tree from 80 yards away very easily. It is very fun to be able to shoot steel up close!

Feel free to ask any questions, request to see additional pictures, or make an offer. Utah buyers must have a current Driver's License or CCW permit; for out-of-staters we will obviously have to go through your FFL dealer. I accept Paypal. Asking $1150 (that is roughly what I paid to put it together), but I will entertain other offers.

Thanks!

title: For Sale:  Mosin Nagant m91 Imperial Tula Finnish Markings Very Good condition!!
postcontent: You are looking at a Collectible Mosin Nagant, this is a gun that possibly saw action in WW1 and WW2 and has fought got 2 different countries. The Gun barrel is an Imperial Tula marked 1896.Most parts are Tula, Outside of the metal butt plate and bolt body which interestingly has a matching serial number to the barrel, this may be an Finnish force match when they acquired the rifle. The stock is unconfirmed, I removed the butt plate but it is very dirty and couldn't identify it. Amongst the markings on the barrel the most interesting are the Finnish Army symbol SA and the large D which denotes the barrel throat opened for the Finnish D166 cartridge. This is a collectible Rifle with much history proven by the markings and being an M91 in excellent condition, maintaining many Tula parts with Finnish Army markings makes for a valuable commodity in your collection. Don't be fooled by the FIME Group rifles, they are not TRUE Arsenal Rifles! I have here for sale or trade a genuine Arsenal stamped sgl-31 61. This is the real deal here. You can not buy these off the shelves anymore because Arsenal US doesn't import the Sgl series rifles anymore, FIME group started imported these models. Therefore, making the Arsenal stamped Sgl-31's extremely rare and collectible! 

The brainchild of two of the best gun makers in the world, the Sgl-31 61 rifle is manufactured at the world famous Izhmash factory in Russia then imported and remanufactured by Arsenal Inc, Las Vegas, NV into its final configuration. The only TRUE configured AK-74 currently available in the US market that uses brand new Hammer Forged and Chrome Lined barrel, the SGL-31 61 offers the safety and reliability that you expect from your rifle, making it the highest quality AK-74 available on the market!

This is the 5.45 caliber, the cheapest high power rifle ammunition out there! A blast to shoot! Highly accurate and low recoil! Check out the YouTube videos on the Sgl-31! 

This rifle has upgraded beautiful wood furniture, rather than the cheap black polymer. It also features tritium night sights, both front post and rear! This rifle functions flawlessly. It has a few hundred rounds through it, and is in great working condition!! 

I will be including about 1200 rounds of 5.45 ammo with the rifle!

In 1942, just before Daisy shut down operations due to steel shortages caused by the World War II war effort, Daisy manufactured its 3rd military style bb gun. It was called the No. 140 Military. The No. 140 was manufactured for a very short period of time.  Only about 30,000 of these guns were made.  The No. 140 featured a bolt action that acted as the guns' safety mechanism and a canvas sling, but no bayonet. The shot tube was the same style as the Red Ryder “Lightning Loader”. This is one of the rarest BB guns due to the low number manufactured and is highly desirable and very rarely comes up for sale. This one is particularly nice as it has the original sling and works. Look carefully at photos to judge condition. Slight dent at end of barrel tube (near where bb shoots out of tube). Both front and rear sights are fully intact. Bolts and nuts come as pictured. Ask questions and we will reply rapidly. I think you will be very pleased with this item.

This particulary auction will be shipped registered mail or with signature confirmation and will be sealed at the shipping office with a video recording made of registration, sealing and shipping.
